			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Swarm Kiting<a name="72048"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 11 05 6:31 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>AE kiting you need AE songs but for Swarm Kiting you need charm and chant dots.  I will use stalkers in PoN because it is the ideal situation.
<br />

<br />
My song line up:
<br />
Disease chant
<br />
Ice chant
<br />
Poison chant
<br />
Fire chant
<br />
Charm
<br />
Selo’s
<br />
Invis
<br />
Cantana
<br />

<br />
1. First, charm a stalker and have him attack another stalker.
<br />
2. The other stalkers will add and beat your pet down fast.
<br />
3. Invis before he dies (10% to 15%) and get ready to be chased by all the stalkers.
<br />
4. Get all of them in a nice tight circle and then cycle through the mobs using the F8 key.
<br />
5. Once you have your old pet targeted chant him down.
<br />
6. Then get two new targets and charm one (don’t stop circling) and toggle to the second one and tell you new pet to attack.
<br />
7. All the other stalkers will agro your new pet but you might have to circle a few more times before they get solid agro.
<br />
8. Now you can stop and watch you pet’s health bar.
<br />
9. Goto step 3
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
