			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Swarm Kiting<a name="72057"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 11 05 10:10 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>One important part is to check the mobs abilities first.  Certain popular charm kiting locations are as simple as 1-9, but a random location may have mobs that usually don't snare/stun but occasionally do... which can get ugly at any level.  Fading doesn't always seem to work when i have a charm pet (and invising to break charm can take more time than you have), so you should get aggro from all the mobs first. If one snares/stuns, you can either fade and try somewhere else, fade and charm the snare/stunner, or just charm the caster and tell it to attack if you are a safe distance away.
<br />
Overall, its alot more fun than chant kiting and looks pretty cool too, but you just have to be more careful when you have 15 mobs coming right for you... chain mezzing a dotted mob will usually get you away from a rare caster, but you cant mez all 15 mobs in a swarm kite.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
