			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Swarm Kiting<a name="72066"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 12 05 5:56 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Couple additional tips:
<br />

<br />
The type of agro that makes the other mobs attack your pet is a very weak agro...even weaker than proximity agro. If you run around using proximity agro to gather up a swarm (that will be used to attack your pet), then some of the mobs will chase YOU instead of attacking your pet. You will need to run around a bit (sometimes circling back near the fighting mobs that are killing your pet) to get those chasing you to go after your pet. If, however, you gather the swarm simply by sending your pet into the fray, and stay back and watch the fun, this shouldn't happen. 
<br />

<br />
Also, you can tab-buffer your pet before you send it in, so you can reaquire it by hitting tab.
<br />

<br />
Make sure you do some damage to the former pet so that you get full exp for the kill. Best to just run in a circle and chant it dead, while the others chase you too. Then, run back a bit, and get a target when they come after you. Run the other way (avoiding the pack), get some distance, and start the charm-attack process again. A hotkey for Pet attack helps... charm a mob, switch targets using F8, then hit your pet attack key in rapid succession.  
<br />

<br />
Getting an insta click invis item helps time charm breaks.
<br />

<br />
Try to pick a landmark where you will kill all the ex pets. At the Stalker camp I ran around the dead tree to finish them off. Then cause your next pet to engage the pack a good distance away from your kill spot, so that you can have some time to go loot up.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
</span></td>
